10/11/2009
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Leaders of countries in the Organisation of the Islamic Conference (OIC) gathered in Istanbul on Monday (November 9th) to discuss ways to boost economic co-operation amid the global financial crisis.
Addressing participants in the forum, Turkish President Abdullah Gul urged better co-operation among members on many fronts.
"Our countries face global challenges such as urbanisation, immigration, industrialisation, negative effects of climate change ...
and serious problems with socio-economic and environmental dimensions," Gul said.
The meeting brought together 11 presidents, three vice-presidents, six prime ministers and 18 ministers from Islamic countries.
(Zaman - 10/11/09;
ISRIA, Hurriyet, MIA, EuropeNews, Press TV - 09/11/09)
